          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Negative gamma1 cross sections obtained in the fits",
                "at several energies in the vicinity of 20.5 MeV",
                "probably result from one of the following causes:",
                " (i) slight inaccuracies in the detector response line",
                "shapes used - for example, in the height or shape of",
                "the tail at lower energies;",
                " (ii) small inaccuracies in the energy calibration, to",
                "which the gamma1 cross section is quite sensitive; or",
                " (iii) incorrect theory - for example, improper",
                "position of the first excited state relative to the",
                "ground state, or extension of the factored wave",
                "function method beyond its region of applicability."
              ]
            }
          ],
